# MLBMA Design Contract

**Full source of truth:** [design/MLBMA_CURSOR_DESIGN_CONTRACT.md](../../design/MLBMA_CURSOR_DESIGN_CONTRACT.md)

Before any dashboard or website UI work, read that file and adapt to the **existing** codebase — do not invent a parallel design system.

## North star

Premium baseball matchup command center: dense, editorial, credible, fast. Violet accent + dark boards. **Green=elite → red=poor** on all metric chips via existing helpers.

Gloss target: the May 2026 ChatGPT-generated MLBMA infographic look translated into the locked system — near-black scouting grid, violet neon edge light, glossy/inset panels, metallic silver display headings, violet gradient emphasis, compact editorial caps, circular glowing icon badges, and illuminated active controls. Aesthetic only; no structure changes.

Icon rule: key MLBMA surfaces should use bold custom poster marks from `dashboard/mlbma_icons.js`; default thin Lucide strokes are only acceptable for small utility controls. High-visibility icons need circular/glowing badge treatment and enough fill/stroke weight to read like the generated infographic icons.

## Project anchors (use these, do not reinvent)

| Layer | Files |
|-------|--------|
| Design system | `dashboard/mlbma_design_system.css`, `dashboard/theme.css`, `dashboard/mlbma_ui.css` |
| Shared helpers | `dashboard/mlbma_assets.js` — `valChipHtml`, `metricColor`, `sectionHeaderHtml`, `caSectionHeadHtml` |
