| Brand (separate rule) | Logos, avatars, nav — `.cursor/rules/chase-brand-and-avatars.mdc` |

## Structure lock (dashboard)

**May change:** chip styling, typography, spacing/density, borders/shadows, section-header polish, class names, tokens.

**Must not change** unless the user explicitly asks: section order, Lineup/SP/Bullpen tabs, DOM hierarchy, data placement, metric definitions, routing, controls, section count.

If a visual idea requires moving data or re-nesting sections → **stop**; ask or scope as structural task.

## Visual rules

- **Tokens first** — `--bg`, `--card`, `--border`, `--v-grad`, `--c-*`; no scattered one-off hex.
- **Typography** — Roboto Condensed (display/headers), DM Sans (UI/numbers); `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`.
- **Metric chips** — solid, high-contrast; always `valChipHtml` / `metricColor`; never per-stat rainbow palettes.
- **Filters** — platform `hub-control-bar` + `hub-pill` active gradient; no flat custom pill overrides.
- **Density** — Rankings-level tight rhythm (~12–16px section gaps, compact boards); avoid triple-wrapped cards and oversized empty space.
- **Data integrity** — honest empty states; no fake production stats.

## Workflow (every UI pass)

1. Read contract + touched owner files.
2. State edit plan: visual vs structural; how structure lock is preserved.
3. Scoped diff in existing files — no new CSS framework, no duplicate component trees.
4. Verify: lint if available, browser smoke test, console clean, responsive check.
5. Report: files changed + confirm structure lock for dashboard aesthetic work:

> Confirmed: dashboard visual changes were styling/class/token changes only. No sections were moved, added, removed, merged, split, or re-nested; Lineup/SP/Bullpen tabs and data placement remain intact.
